"{\n  \"judgement\": \"The argument that parents have a responsibility to teach their children their own beliefs, rather than imposing their own, is more defensible than the blanket claim that all parental indoctrination is inherently bad.\",\n  \"steering\": \"It seems like we're all trying to protect our kids from misinformation. Can we focus on sharing resources or perspectives that promote critical thinking and media literacy, rather than getting bogged down in who's 'indoctrinating' whom?\"}"